THE STUDENT PILOT WAS PERFORMING A CROSSWIND LANDING WHICH RESULTED IN 
A HARD LANDING. THE AIRCRAFT DRIFTED TO THE SIDE OF THE RUNWAY AND ONE WHEEL 
WAS OFF THE PAVED SURFACE UPON THE NEXT TOUCHDOWN. THE STUDENT PILOT 
ATTEMPTED TO HOLD THE AIRCRAFT STRAIGHT IN THE DIRECTION IT WAS GOING. THE 
NOSE WHEEL DROPPED IN A SHALLOW DITCH AND THE AIRCRAFT NOSED OVER. 
